				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've already got my 30 AA saved.
<br />

<br />
I'm DEFINATELY doing this path.
<br />

<br />
Pet flurry
<br />
Pet crit
<br />
Secondary Forte
<br />
Pet durability
<br />
Pet agility
<br />
Fury of Magic Mastery
<br />
Pet Affinity
<br />
Persistent Casting
<br />
Shared Health
<br />

<br />
Ok, now before you call me crazy, the reason i've decided to go with this is as follows.  I do a shitload of LDoN, and PoFire table kite groups.  Both of these things are very pet heavy, neither of which, the pet ever really tanks in (unless i'm pulling in LDoN and have my pet off tank while the tank wakes up to notice a mob there, only in easy though).
<br />

<br />
So the pet damage AA's will hopefully give me a pretty good edge, Some may say i'd be better off investing in new crits, however, i'd rather upgrade the damage done via my pets first, so that this damage upgrade is less restricted by agro, if you follow.
<br />

<br />
Secondary forte is next so I can use FoT and rains without feeling guilty about my horrendous mana consumption.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=339789" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vicour1/AnduranSig.jpg" border="0" /></a>
